text: Anarsia lewvanichae is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by Kyu-Tek Park and Margarita Gennadievna Ponomarenko in 1996. It is found in Thailand. The wingspan is about 10.5 mm. The forewings are yellowish white speckled brown scales and a large dark brown costal mark. The hindwings are grey. ==References== lewvanichae Category:Moths described in 1996 Category:Moths of Asia
